Three persons, two boys and a girl, died in a road accident along Oba Ile Road, Akure North Local government area. Three other persons were said to have been seriously injured in the accident that occurred on Thursday evening. The accident involved a Toyota Corolla car marked Lagos APP 91 GR and a Mercedes Benz Bullion Van belonging to the Central Bank of Nigeria (CBN) marked Ondo JTA 478 AA. Witnesses said the car was heading to Oba Ile while the bullion van was going to Akure. Driver of the Toyota Corolla was said to have lost control, skidded over the road divider and rammed into the bullion van. The witnesses said three corpses were brought out of the car. Officials of the Federal Road Safety Corps and the Nigeria Police Force were seen at the scene to clear the debris.